-- NHL’s Malkin, Gonchar Sign Lock-Out Deals With Russian Team
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-09-16T11:19:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-16/nhl-s-malkin-gonchar-sign-lock-out-deals-with-russian-team.html
National Hockey League all-stars
Evengi Malkin and Sergei Gonchar have signed deals allowing them
to play for  Russia ’s Magnitogorsk Metallurg in the event of a
work stoppage in the North American league, according to the
Kontinental Hockey League club’s  website .  The agreements fall within the scope of rules set by the
league allowing ice time to players under contract in the NHL,
according to the Metallurg statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow at 
